(
<figureCitation id="135AC5F00D4BFF8EFF75111126B2CA61" box="[160,241,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[391,1197,748,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-233@6.[391,1197,740,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Body, dorsal view: (17) Balacha ancora sp. nov., male (length 4.8 mm); (18) Balacha nigroflava sp. nov., male (l. 5.8 mm); (19) Balacha rubripennis Cavichioli &amp; Sakakibara, 1988, male (l. 9.4 mm). (20) Balacha ancora sp. nov. on a leaf of Actinocephalus polyanthus (Bong.) Sano (Eriocaulaceae) at Parque Nacional da Serra do Cipó, Minas Gerais State (1,279 m a.s.l.); photo: André Almeida Alves, October 10, 2019." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4425450" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4425450/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="552">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDED9750D4BFF8EFF4211A925F4C9AD" blockId="10.[151,1437,1411,1905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis id="B91505670D4BFF8EFF4211A926A2CAA9" bold="true" box="[151,225,1411,1437]" pageId="10" pageNumber="552">Notes.</emphasis>
We have studied Argentinian specimens that have a color pattern similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C61A2F60D4BFF8EFBFE11A922D3CAA9" authorityName="Cavichioli &amp; Sakakibara" authorityYear="1988" box="[1067,1168,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balacha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis id="B91505670D4BFF8EFBFE11A922D3CAA9" box="[1067,1168,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="552">B. lepida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but their male terminalia indicate that they belong in 
<taxonomicName id="4C61A2F60D4BFF8EFE25118D24D1CAF5" authorityName="Cavichioli &amp; Sakakibara" authorityYear="1988" box="[496,658,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balacha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubripennis">
<emphasis id="B91505670D4BFF8EFE25118D24D1CAF5" box="[496,658,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="552">B. rubripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These specimens have the ground color of the anterior dorsum (head and pronotum) orange to red with dark brown to black markings as follows: anterior margin of crown with two large spots; posterior margin of crown with pair of maculae extending to ocelli; broad macula over coronal suture; anterior margin of pronotum with two large spots, posterior margin with broad transverse macula connected to median stripe, the latter linked laterally to anterior pair of spots; pronotum with smaller macula behind each compound eye and extending to posterior margin. Mesonotum almost entirely dark brown to black, delimiting pair of oblique orange to red areas. Forewing mostly dark orange to red, without spots.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
